Reading 37

Todays reading was on the topic of python for pen-testers and why they should choose python,
one of the reasons that python should be used is because it a general purpose interpreter programming
language, it OO but also supports functional programming. Some of the reasons pen-tester use python is
because Python supports a wealth of libraries that are very useful in helping pen-testers accomplish 
their task, the article list of the top five top libraries for testers which are Impacket, Python Nmap,
Scapy, BeautifulSoup and Mona which all provide values in there own ways but used together can help uncover
even more insight for pesters the navigate and gain information about systems. 
